<refentry id="xpf_urlify">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>urlify</refentrytitle>
    <refmiscinfo>XPATH</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>urlify</refname>
    <refpurpose>Converts its argument to a string and returns it in URL encoding.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <funcsynopsis id="xpf_syn_urlify">
      <funcprototype id="xpf_proto_urlify">
        <funcdef>string <function>urlify</function></funcdef>
	<paramdef><parameter>obj</parameter> string</paramdef>
      </funcprototype>
    </funcsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1 id="xpf_desc_urlify"><title>Description</title>
    <para>The urlify() function encodes its argument string according to
URI rules (i.e. whitespaces are replaced with plus signs and all special characters
are replaced with '%XX' notation. This is especially useful for stylesheets
that compose dynamic HTML documents with calculateable values of
attributes like &lt;A HREF=...&gt;.
    </para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1 id="xpf_params_urlify"><title>Parameters</title>
    <refsect2><title>obj</title><para>Value to be formatted as URI</para></refsect2>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1 id="xpf_ret_urlify"><title>Return Types</title><para>String</para></refsect1>
